  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dda \u0db8\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A death in the gas line",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kottawa police said that a person who was waiting in a gas queue at the Kottawa bus station died today (12th) after being admitted to the Homagama base hospital for treatment due to a sudden medical condition.",
        "The police say that Jayatissa Perera (63), a resident of 1015 Liyanagoda Road, Kottawa, is an electrical engineer.",
        "This person is said to have gone with his son to a Litro gas distribution point which was organized at the main bus stand in Kottawa city center this morning.",
        "For that, a large number of people had come and waited in the queue and the deceased person also came to the place in a car and waited there expecting to buy a gas cylinder.",
        "The police said that this person, who fell ill along with the people staying there, was taken to the Homagama Base Hospital for treatment and later died while receiving treatment there.",
        "The post-mortem examination of the body of the deceased person is to be conducted by the Homagama Coroner Justice of the Peace Mr. Chinthaka Udayakumara at the Homagama Basic Hospital's Accident Investigation Court."
      ],
